(141, '', 'Atomos Shinobi SDI 5\" 3G-SDI & 4K HDMI Pro Monitor', 6, 20, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Atomos', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Key Features<br />\r\n1920 x 1080 Touchscreen Display<br />\r\n3G-SDI &amp; 4K HDMI Inputs<br />\r\nDaylight-Viewable Monitor<br />\r\n1000 cd/m&sup2; Brightness</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Atomos Shinobi SDI 5&quot; 3G-SDI &amp; 4K HDMI Pro Monitor</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Introducing Shinobi SDI</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Atomos Shinobi SDI is a lightweight HDR field monitor for the video professional who needs the flexibility of both HDMI and SDI camera connectivity, or the vlogger wanting to take their production to the next level. Connect 4K HDMI for HDR viewing or SDI for HD-SDI loop out. Run cables between Shinobi SDIs up to 100m (328ft) without degradation of image allowing directors, crew and clients to see what the camera operator is seeing in stunning detail. Shinobi SDI&#39;s high brightness 1000nit 5-inch monitor lets crew members preview and see images exactly as intended in any lighting condition, in SDR or HDR. Shinobi SDI is the ultimate monitoring tool in your video production arsenal that won&rsquo;t break the bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDR monitoring made easy</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shinobi SDI is our first stand-alone compact SDI-capable HDR monitor for professionals where recording capability is not required. It is built to match your high-end cinema and production cameras and can run all day on a single battery. It features all our amazing screen-processing technology and creative simple-to-use monitoring-tools including the new multi-tool &lsquo;Analysis&rsquo;, designed for perfect real-time image checking. Set your shots up accurately using advanced histograms, waveforms or video scopes; all while seeing what your camera sees.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Compatible in every situation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Shinobi SDI supports up to 4KDCIp30 HDMI and HDp60 SDI in and out to connect to cameras, broadcast monitors, switchers &amp; recorders. HDMI is perfect for DSLRs, mirrorless, video cameras, phones and tablets. SDI gives Shinobi SDI the advantage of connecting to any existing SD or HD infrastructure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The 5&rdquo; SDI monitor that packs a punch</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a stunning 5&rdquo; 10-bit HDR or SDR display, the Shinobi SDI allows you to see your images clearly in daylight with the near edge-to-edge 1000nit anti-reflection screen. The sleek light-weight design is crafted for maximum efficiency and weighing in at just 226g/7.8oz, it is one of the lightest 4K SDI and HDMI monitors on the market, stealthily attaching to any SDI &amp; HDMI camera setup.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zoom Up to 4:1&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Input Resolution (up to)&nbsp; 4096x2048</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Screen 1920x1080</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Connection (up to) HDMI 1.4b/3.5G SDI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The best&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>of AtomOS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Shinobi SDI utilizes our revolutionary AtomOS 10 platform, packed with an extensive suite of scopes and one touch simple operations. Shinobi SDI includes monitoring tools for focus, framing &amp; exposure, including Focus Peaking, 4:1 / 2:1 / 1:1 Zoom, Zebra, False Color, Frame Guides, SMPTE Safe Area, Waveform, Histogram, RGB parade, Vectorscope, Anamorphic De-squeeze, new multi-view &lsquo;Analysis&rsquo; mode and more. Each feature customizable and interchangeable in size, best suiting the Shinobi SDI user.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>&#39;Analysis&#39; mode -</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>powerful and simple</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>At Atomos, we understand how crucial it is to always see what you&rsquo;re shooting. With the new &lsquo;Analysis&rsquo; mode, view a waveform, histogram, vectorscope while simultaneously shooting all at the same time; ensuring complete control of your image. Try switching between different waveform, histogram and vector scope options on the fly with a single touch; adjusting all scopes with a single touch &ndash; simple.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Real-time HDR in the field</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Shinobi SDI screen utilizes the AtomHDR processing engine to displaying a stunning 10+ stops of dynamic range in real-time from Log/PQ or HLG signals; wide color-gamut mapping ensures the perfect image color is always displayed. Combined with our unique HDR monitoring features, the Shinobi SDI simplifies complexities of shooting Log and HDR, helping replicate a post-production workflow the moment it matters most, while shooting. We look after the technology, so you can focus on the storytelling.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Instant LUT preview</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Apply and compare your favorite looks for your camera or from your post-production team; achieving consistency in SDR or HDR across all shoots. The Shinobi SDI allows you to load internally up to eight custom LUTs, looks or profiles at any time via the SD Card Slot and instantly select between them, maintaining creative intent, always.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Calibrated true-to-eye colors</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Accurate color-representation is key to trustworthy monitoring. Color calibrate your Shinobi SDI for ongoing accurate HDR and SDR (Rec.709) monitoring.* Color and brightness accuracy on monitors drifts over time. Calibration ensures accurate image representation at all times. Simply download the Mac/PC Atomos Calibration app. Purchase our USB to Serial cable to connect to the Shinobi SDI and gain peace of mind when in the field.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>*X-Rite&rsquo;s i1 Display Pro calibrator</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Longer battery life</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Designed exclusively for monitoring purposes, the Shinobi requires very low power &ndash; either in standby or while monitoring. Lasting round-the-clock on a single battery, have certainty with uninterrupted endurance. Longer monitoring times are covered with the in-the-box free AC adaptor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The ultimate live production companion</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>In a live production environment, it is important that behind every camera, the operator has the highest quality monitoring. The SDI and HDMI connections allow for an infinite array of connectivity with other Atomos products; allowing the user to simply and efficiently create the ultimate production environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Designed for every situation</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>When attached to your camera, the size and weight of your monitor matters. We shaved the Shinobi down to just 222g (7.8oz) and added &frac14;&rdquo;-20 screw mounts top and bottom for easy cage and adaptor rigging; making the Shinobi compatible with most SDI and HDMI-ready devices. The centre-mounting battery makes balancing easy and manoeuvrability instant.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Affordable, professional&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4K HDMI &amp; HD-SDI monitor</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>At just $US499, the Atomos Shinobi SDI matches any camera level, and is one of the most affordable HDR SDI monitors available today.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\n<strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">Weight</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Without batteries</td>\r\n			<td>226g / 7.8oz.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Dimensions (W x H x D mm)</td>\r\n			<td>151 x 91.5 x 31.5mm</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Construction</td>\r\n			<td>Polycarbonate ABS</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Mounting points</td>\r\n			<td>1/4&rdquo;-20 screw mount. 1x top and 1x bottom</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">Power</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Operating power</td>\r\n			<td>4 - 7W</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Compatible batteries</td>\r\n			<td>NP-F series and supporting accessories. AtomX or other.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Input voltage (battery)</td>\r\n			<td>6.2V to 16.8V</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Battery time&nbsp;<br />\r\n			(based on 7.4V)</td>\r\n			<td><strong>Standby</strong><br />\r\n			2600mAh - 3hrs, 5200mAh - 6hrs, 7800mAh - 12hrs</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td><strong>Monitor</strong><br />\r\n			2600mAh - 1.5hrs, 5200mAh - 3hrs, 7800mAh - 6hrs</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>DC In</td>\r\n			<td>via Battery Eliminator</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">Touchscreen</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Size</td>\r\n			<td>5.2&rdquo;</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Resolution</td>\r\n			<td>1920 x 1080</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>PPI</td>\r\n			<td>427</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Aspect ratio</td>\r\n			<td>16:9 native</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Color Gamut</td>\r\n			<td>REC709 HDTV</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Look up table (LUT) support</td>\r\n			<td>3D LUT (.cube format) *Extended Support planned</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Anamorphic de-squeeze</td>\r\n			<td>2x, 1.5x, 1.33x</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Technology</td>\r\n			<td>IPS panel (capacitive touch), calibration to Rec.709 with optional calibration unit</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">HDR</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>AtomHDR</td>\r\n			<td>Yes</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>HDR Monitoring (Gamut)</td>\r\n			<td>Sony SLog / SLog2 / SLog3, Canon CLog / CLog2 / Clog3,<br />\r\n			Arri Log CEI160 / LogCEI200 / LogCEI250 / LogCEI320<br />\r\n			/ LogCEI400 / LogCEI500 / LogCEI640 / LogCEI800 /<br />\r\n			LogCEI1000 / LogCEI1280 / LogCEI1600, Panasonic Vlog,<br />\r\n			JVC JLog1, RED Log3G10 /RED LogFilm, FujiFilm F-log,<br />\r\n			PQ10k, HLG, Nikon N-Log</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>HDR Monitoring (Gamma)</td>\r\n			<td>Sony SGamut / SGamut3 / SGamut3.cine<br />\r\n			Canon Cinema / DCI P3 / DCI P3+<br />\r\n			Panasonic V Gamut<br />\r\n			Arri Alexa Wide Gamut<br />\r\n			Rec709 / BT.2020<br />\r\n			JVC<br />\r\n			RED WideGamut / RED DragonColor / DragonColor2 /&nbsp;<br />\r\n			RED Color2 / RED Color3 / RED Color4</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Bit Depth</td>\r\n			<td>10-bit (8+2 FRC)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Brightness</td>\r\n			<td>1000nit (+/- 10%)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Screen Mirror/Flip</td>\r\n			<td>Horizontal Flip (Selfie mode), Vertical Flip<br />\r\n			* Landscape/Portrait mode planned for future firmware release</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Anti-reflective</td>\r\n			<td>Special AR coating and Anti-fingerprint technology</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">Video Input</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>SDI</td>\r\n			<td>1 x HD-SDI 1.3G/1.5G</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>HDMI</td>\r\n			<td>1 x HDMI (1.4)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Signal</td>\r\n			<td>Up to Uncompressed true 10-bit or 8-bit 422<br />\r\n			(camera dependent)</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">Supported Formats (Video Input)</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>2k DCI 2048 x 1080</td>\r\n			<td>23.98p, 24p, 25p, 29.97p, 50p, 59.97p</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>UHD 3840 x 2160<br />\r\n			&nbsp;</td>\r\n			<td>23.98p, 24p, 25p, 29.97p</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>HD 1920 x 1080</td>\r\n			<td>23.98p, 24p, 25p, 29.97p, 50p, 59.94p</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>HD 1280 x 720</td>\r\n			<td>50p, 59.94p</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">Audio In (48kHz)</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>HDMI</td>\r\n			<td>2ch 24-bit 48kHz</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>SDI</td>\r\n			<td>8ch 24-bit 48kHz</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">Audio Out</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Headphone out</td>\r\n			<td>3.5mm</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">SD Card Slot</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Full size SD Card slot</td>\r\n			<td>SD Card Slot allows LUTs to be loaded to the unit and is also used when updating AtomOS firmware</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">AtomOS</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Monitoring Features</td>\r\n			<td>Luma Waveform, RGB parade, RGB Overlay, Vectorscope, Vectorscope Zoom, Histogram, RGB Histogram, Anlaysis mode (Multiview scopes: Waveform, Histogram, Vectorscope), Focus Peaking, Zebra, False Color, Blue Only Exposure, Zoom (1:1, 2:1, 4:1), SMPTE Safe Areas, Cinema Guides, Anamorphic Desqueeze.</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n	<thead>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<th colspan=\"2\">What&#39;s In The Box</th>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</thead>\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Included</td>\r\n			<td>Shinobi SDI unit,&nbsp;<br />\r\n			12V-15W AC power supply,&nbsp;<br />\r\n			Quick Start guide</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Optional Accessories</td>\r\n			<td><strong>Power Kit:</strong>&nbsp;2 x NP-F Batteries,<br />\r\n			1 x charger, 1 x power supply&nbsp;<br />\r\n			<strong>AtomX 5&rdquo; Cage for Shinobi SDI&nbsp;</strong>(by SmallRig)<br />\r\n			<strong>AtomX 5&rdquo; Sunhood&nbsp;</strong>(compatible w. Shinobi SDI / Ninja V)<br />\r\n			<strong>AtomX 5&rdquo; Screen Protector&nbsp;</strong>(compatible w. Shinobi SDI / Ninja V)<br />\r\n			<strong>AtomX 10&rdquo; Arm &amp; Quick Release Plate&nbsp;</strong>(by Lanparte)<br />\r\n			<br />\r\n			Other:<br />\r\n			<strong>Atomos HDMI cables</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>Xrite i1 Display Pro Calibrator and USB to Serial cable</strong><br />\r\n			<strong>AtomX 5&rdquo; Accessory Kit</strong></td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td>Warranty</td>\r\n			<td>1 year</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n	</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n', '1612201620285fda33cc1bdd4.jpg', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:20:28', 0, '2020-12-16 16:20:28'),
(142, '', 'Atomos Ninja V 5\" 4K HDMI Recording Monitor', 6, 20, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Atomos', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Key Features<br />\r\n1920 x 1080 Touchscreen Display<br />\r\n10-Bit Exterior Viewable Monitor<br />\r\n4K HDMI Input<br />\r\n1000 cd/m&sup2; Brightness</p>\r\n', '1612201623315fda3483aa875.jpg', 29900, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:23:31', 0, '2020-12-16 16:23:31'),
(143, '', 'Atomos NEON HDR Cinema Monitor-Recorder for on-set and in-studio', 6, 20, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Atomos', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Atomos NEON HDR Cinema Monitor-Recorder for on-set and in-studio</strong><br />\r\n<strong>neon 55&quot; ,neon 31&quot;,neon 24&quot;, neon 17&quot;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Digital filmmaking re-imagined</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>for today&rsquo;s creator</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Atomos Neon series is the beginning of a new journey for filmmakers by bringing together traditional filmmaking roles and pairing it with Atomos innovation and technology. We do this by combining RAW recording with cinema display technology for monitoring, on-screen production checking and review of creative intent, story flow and matching continuity between scenes. Neon streamlines the creative workflow from lens to viewing. We have adopted industry standard formats like ProRes RAW from major camera makers enabling the performance of ProRes and the flexibility of RAW into cinema productions and built for computer finishing. Neon performs real-time Dolby Vision processing to enable down-stream viewing on any Dolby Vision capable TV or monitor. The upshot is an on-set computer replacement merged with an ecosystem of field monitors that saves the creator time by allowing them to make more decisions in the moment of recording, playback, monitoring and editing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Certainty of image&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>for the entire crew</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Neon is a series of precision on-set and in-studio 4K HDR monitor-recorder production workhorses where reliable and trustworthy monitoring is essential. The Neon comes in four sizes (17&rdquo;, 24&rdquo;, 31&rdquo; and 55&rdquo;) that can be synced together to provide an ecosystem of field monitors where accuracy of image representation and consistency of image is critical between crew members...all controlled by the Atomos App. The Neons&rsquo; best-in-class 512 zoned dynamic backlight displays provide a calibrated 4KDCI 180-degree perfect viewing, 10-bit DCI-P3 100% color coverage, and 1,000,000:1 HDR-ready contrast for cinematographers to maintain exposure and creative look. Directors can make more creative on-set decisions, viewing perfect images in TV and Cinema standards at all times. Camera assistants and focus pullers can trust the ultra-sharpness of an actor&#39;s eyes. Editors and color graders can lock down the director&rsquo;s creative intent from shot to shot, frame by frame and review it across varying displays from SDR to HDR &ndash; accurately in real-time. With the built-in 4Kp60/HDp240 Apple ProRes RAW recorder capturing each take, Neon enables quick review and real-time playout with Dolby Vision to reality test content on domestic TVs. With Neon, Atomos has reimagined the role of the reference monitor to meet the HDR challenges of modern TV and film production.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ATOMOS NEON HDR Cinema Monitor-Recorder for on-set and in-studio รุ่นนี้ออกมาด้วยกัน 4 ขนาด&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- neon 55&quot; Resolution 3840x2160 16:9&nbsp; &nbsp;ppi 84&nbsp; Backlights 512</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- neon 31&quot; Resolution 4096x2160 17:9&nbsp; &nbsp;ppi 147 Backlights 512</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- neon 24&quot; Resolution 4096x2160 17:9&nbsp; &nbsp;ppi 193 Backlights 512</p>\r\n\r\n<p>- neon 17&quot; Resolution 2048x1080 17:9&nbsp; &nbsp; ppi 128 Backlights 128</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Four sizes for flexibility in any production</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Neon comes in 17&rdquo;, 24&rdquo;, 31&rdquo; and 55&rdquo; screen sizes, and complements other Atomos products such as the Shinobi SDI, Ninja V, Shogun 7 and Sumo 19 to provide a flexible ecosystem of field reference monitors. Neon allows you the flexibility of utilizing your Atomos on low budget productions with HDMI 10-bit uncompressed video cameras, right up to 12G-SDI 12-Bit, 4Kp60 RAW from the best cinema cameras in the world.</p>\r\n', '1612201626145fda3526c4d95.jpg', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:26:14', 0, '2020-12-16 16:26:14'),
(144, '', 'Atomos AtomX SDI Module for Ninja V', 6, 20, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Atomos', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Key Features<br />\r\nAdds Two 12G-SDI Ports to Ninja V<br />\r\nSDI Ports Are User Configurable<br />\r\nSupports 4K60p and 2K240p<br />\r\nNumerous Playback Options, Including HDR</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Atomos AtomX SDI Module for Ninja V</strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe Atomos AtomX SDI Module for Ninja V brings 12-G SDI I/O to your Ninja V monitor/recorder. The module supports 4K at up to 60p as well as 2K at up to 240p and is a simple addition to your Ninja V, mounting to the expansion port in the battery slot. The 12-G ports are user assignable as input or output and support industry standard DI formats. The AtomX provides numerous playback options including HDR. The AtomX passes power from an L-series battery to your Ninja V without significantly increasing the footprint of your Ninja V.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Modularity is at the heart of the Ninja V with a bi-directional high speed expansion port breaking out connectivity for I/O of video, audio and power. Atomos created AtomX to ensure users could adapt and connect to any legacy or future wireless or wired video standard. The expansion system offers endless scalability and is demonstrated by the first of many modules - the AtomX Ethernet/NDI&reg; at $199 and the AtomX Sync at $149.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>AtomX SDI</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The AtomX SDI expansion module is designed to turn your Atomos Ninja V into a pro video SDI powerhouse. The module adds the quality and convenience of SDI equipment and infrastructure connectivity in addition to its existing HDMI capability. Monitor and record SDI up to 4Kp60, and go into or out of any SDI device including the popular Atomos Shinobi SDI pro monitor and Atomos Shogun Inferno, as well as legacy Atomos SDI products. This provides flexibility for any video or film production to allow all crew including directors, cinematographers, assistants and focus pullers to monitor and replay identical and calibrated content in HDR at the same time.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SDI In/Out Up to 12Gb/s</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>AtomX Port 32Gb/s</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Stack &amp; Lock&nbsp;Design System</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Simultaneous In/Out 2x6G, 2x3G</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>AtomX Ethernet/NDI</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The AtomX Ethernet/NDI module has a wired ethernet (1 GigE) connector that makes it possible to deliver live broadcast-grade video over IP networks. Newtek&rsquo;s NDI technology harnesses this - allowing for simple installation and control of multi-camera networks, replacing traditional SDI cabling. The AtomX Ethernet/NDI module has NDI input and output with encode, decode, control and sync, allowing Ninja V users to transmit, distribute or receive and monitor NDI from any NDI source. Simply power on the Ninja V with AtomX Ethernet/NDI module installed, plug in your network cable, and your source will be automatically discovered on the NDI network ready for production.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>In/Outs HDMI/1GigE</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ethernet 1Gb/s</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDMI 2.0 4Kp60</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Channels 6+</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Channels over 10G 100</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Encode/Decode NDI HDp60</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Latency &lt; 30ms</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDR/SDR</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>AtomX SYNC</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The AtomX Sync module brings professional wireless timecode and sync plus Bluetooth control to Ninja V, perfect for enhancing DSLRs, mirrorless cameras or game recordings. You can sync and/or control literally thousands of Ninja V units equipped with AtomX Sync modules on the same network at ranges of up to 300m. Multi-cam shoots have never been so easy. AtomX modules bring broadcast level standards to any HDMI camera or source, making it easy to integrate large sensor consumer cameras easily into traditional live productions. AtomX Sync has a built-in battery extender that allows for continuous power when swapping batteries, ensuring uninterrupted operation of the Ninja V during a shoot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Range 300m</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequency 1GHz/Bluetooth</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Timecode Sync</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frame Rate 60p, HD/4K</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Control Master/slave</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Networked Devices 1000+</strong><br />\r\n<strong>Continuous Power 7 mins</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Class leading technology partnerships</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The beauty of licensing technology from Newtek and Timecode Systems is that all their products are fully compatible with the relevant AtomX modules &ndash; so large and small productions currently using NDI&rsquo;s or Timecode Systems&rsquo; class leading products can effortlessly integrate Atomos devices. The simplest application with Newtek is integration with their famous TriCaster products.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Timecode systems the most basic use case is to sync a mirrorless camera to an appropriately equipped audio device for perfect automated sync sound &ndash; a huge benefit for anyone from vloggers through to broadcasters and Hollywood productions.</p>\r\n', '1612201626495fda3549f19b6.jpg', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:26:49', 0, '2020-12-16 16:26:49'),
(145, '', 'Atomos Shogun 7 HDR Pro Monitor/Recorder', 6, 20, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Atomos', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Key Features<br />\r\n7&quot; 1920 x 1280 Touchscreen Display<br />\r\nDynamic AtomHDR, 360-Zone Backlight<br />\r\n4 x 3G-SDI, 2 x 12G-SDI<br />\r\n4K HDMI Input/Output</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Atomos Shogun 7 HDR Pro Monitor/Recorder</strong><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Unbelievable HDR, real-time</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Dolby Vision monitoring</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Atomos Shogun 7 is a precision HDR monitor-recorder-switcher designed for the film and video professional. It can be used as either a stand-alone field monitor, recorder and switcher for event, documentary and live in-the-field storytelling; or as a tool for large-scale on-set episodic TV, film and cinema productions where multiple crew members such as focus pullers, grips and cinematographers require a consistent visual reference across the field monitor ecosystem. Shogun 7&#39;s portable size lets you monitor, analyze and tag while on set; and check how your content will look in your audience&rsquo;s home via real-time Dolby Vision output. With Shogun 7 you&rsquo;re not locked into any format, camera manufacturer or pipeline. It is a completely flexible master recording and production station.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Screen Size 7.2&quot;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrast Rate 1,000,000:1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dynamic AtomHDR 360 Zones 15+ Stops</p>\r\n\r\n<p>High Bright 1500nits</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Resolution 1920x1280</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Live Video Streams 4xISO, 1xProgram</p>\r\n', '1612201628335fda35b13733e.jpg', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:28:33', 0, '2020-12-16 16:28:33'),
(146, '', 'ATOMOS HDMI CABLES 4K 60P', 6, 20, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Atomos', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ATOMOS HDMI CABLES 4K 60P</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Ensure your HDMI cables aren&rsquo;t the weakest link on set. Featuring high quality connectors, high speed HDMI 2.0 for the latest high frame rate recordings and a coiled cable for neater cable management on the rig. These are the only HDMI cables specifically designed for filmmakers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDMI 2.0 READY</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Passes the high speed tests laid out in HDMI 2.0. 4Kp60 and HD 240p are fully supported.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDR READY</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Compatible with High Dynamic Range (HDR) product line up.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>4KP60 READY</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The perfect cable for Atomos Inferno and connecting other high frame rate 4Kp60 ProRes and Raw infrastructure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ATOMFLEX COILED CABLE</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Coiled cable to give flexibility on the rig, extending &amp; retracting as you need to minimize clutter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://fv.lnwfile.com/_/fv/_raw/sy/t4/bp.jpg\" style=\"height:227px; width:779px\" /></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDMI CABLES</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>ATOM4K60C1&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;HDMI Full HDMI Micro (die cast metal) Coiled&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;30cm coiled (60cm extended)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ATOM4K60C2HDMI FullHDMI Micro (die cast metal) Coiled40cm coiled (80cm extended)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ATOM4K60C3 HDMI Full HDMI Mini (die cast metal)&nbsp; &nbsp;Coiled 30cm coiled (60cm extended)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ATOM4K60C4 HDMI Full HDMI Mini (die cast metal) &nbsp;Coiled 40cm coiled (80cm extended)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ATOM4K60C5 HDMI Full HDMI Full (die cast metal) &nbsp;Coiled 30cm coiled (60cm extended)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>ATOM4K60C6 HDMI Full HDMI Full (die cast metal) &nbsp;Coiled 40cm coiled (80cm extended)</p>\r\n', '1612201629355fda35efd4e87.jpg', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:29:35', 0, '2020-12-16 16:29:35'),
(147, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput Q5 5.5 นิ้ว Full HD On-Camera Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>&nbsp;Lilliput Q5 5.5&quot; Full HD On-Camera Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>5.5&quot; 1920 x 1080 SDI/HDMI Monitor</li>\r\n	<li>450 cd/m&sup2; Brightness</li>\r\n	<li>1000:1 Contrast Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>Built-In SDI/HDMI Cross Conversion</li>\r\n	<li>Waveform, Vectorscope, and Histogram</li>\r\n	<li>Focus Peaking</li>\r\n	<li>False Color</li>\r\n	<li>Pixel-to-Pixel Mapping</li>\r\n	<li>Includes NP-F and LP-E6 Battery Plates</li>\r\n	<li>Includes Shoe Mount &amp; Sun Hood</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Compact, yet fully featured, Lilliput&#39;s Q5 5.5&quot; Full HD</strong>&nbsp;On-Camera Monitor is designed to take on almost any production. The 1920 x 1080 LCD screen packs 401 pixels-per-inch for seamless viewing of Full HD signals. HDMI and SDI inputs on the rear are compatible with DSLRs, mirrorless cameras, and professional camcorders. HDMI and SDI signals can even be cross converted to ensure compatibility with a wide range of workflows.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>NP-F and LP-E6 battery plates are included, and other types of plates are separately available. NP-F and LP-E6 batteries are widely available and are used on many cameras and camcorders, so you should never be without power. When shooting outdoors, the included sun hood makes the screen easier to see by blocking any glare. Lastly, an included articulating shoe mount allows you to secure the Q5 to your camera via a standard accessory shoe and position it after-the-fact.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Full HD Display</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Full HD display on the Q5 enables a 1080p signal to be viewed natively. Monitoring for critical focus on HD productions is a straightforward process, with no &quot;punching in&quot; and losing your original framing. A 1000:1 contrast ratio, 8-bit color depth, and 450 cd/m&sup2; brightness offer a high-quality viewing experience.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Durable Construction</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the unit itself is manufactured from metal, a silicone rubber bumper is included. The bumper prevents scuffing and other damage that may occur from drops or bumps that are too often known during life on set. It even has a small built-in, unobtrusive sun hood which can be mounted directly on top of the bumper in especially bright conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDMI/SDI Cross Conversion</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Take the Q5 on nearly any gig, ranging from low-budget to professional with the built-in HDMI/SDI cross conversion. HDMI signals can be converted to SDI and vice versa, ensuring that the Q5 is compatible with almost any digital video equipment, from consumer to broadcast-grade.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Monitoring Tools</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Analyze the incoming video signal with built-in video monitoring tools to achieve correct exposure, focus, and color balance. Built-in functions include:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Timecode display</p>\r\n\r\n<p>YRGB column</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pixel-to-pixel mapping</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Vectorscope</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Waveform</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Audio level meters</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Focus peaking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>False color</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Histogram</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zebra</p>\r\n\r\n<p>R/G/B only</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Color bars</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Image flip</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display</li>\r\n	<li>Size 5.5&quot; / 14 cm</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution 1920 x 1080</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:9</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 450 cd/m&sup2;</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast Ratio 1000:1</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle 160&deg;/160&deg; (H/V)</li>\r\n	<li>I/O</li>\r\n	<li>Inputs 1 x BNC, 3G/HD/SD-SDI</li>\r\n	<li>1 x HDMI Type A</li>\r\n	<li>Outputs 1 x BNC, 3G/HD/SD-SDI</li>\r\n	<li>1 x HDMI Type A</li>\r\n	<li>1 x 3.5 mm analog stereo audio (headphone)</li>\r\n	<li>SDI Format Support SMPTE-125M, SMPTE-292M, SMPTE-296M, SMPTE-372M, SMPTE-425M (Level A and B), ITU-R BT.656</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Supported Resolutions:</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>1080p 23.98/24/25/29.97/30/50/59.94/60</li>\r\n	<li>1080PsF 23.98/24</li>\r\n	<li>1080i 23.98/24/25/29.97/30/50/59.94/60</li>\r\n	<li>720p 23.98/24/25/29.97/30/50/59.94/60</li>\r\n	<li>NTSC</li>\r\n	<li>PAL</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI Format Support 1080p</li>\r\n	<li>1080i</li>\r\n	<li>720p</li>\r\n	<li>576p</li>\r\n	<li>480p</li>\r\n	<li>NTSC</li>\r\n	<li>PAL</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Power 7&ndash;24 VDC, 1 A</li>\r\n	<li>Power Consumption 12 W maximum</li>\r\n	<li>Environmental Operating Temperature: -4 to 140&deg;F / -20 to 60&deg;C</li>\r\n	<li>Storage Temperature: -22 to 158&deg;F / -30 to 70&deg;C</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions 6.1 x 3.5 x 0.8&quot; / 15.4 x 9.0 x 2.0 cm</li>\r\n	<li>Weight 0.7 lb / 320 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201636565fda37a856900.jpg', 17500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:36:56', 0, '2020-12-16 16:36:56'),
(148, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 569/O นิ้ว On-Camera Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ &nbsp;Lilliput 569/O 5&quot; On-Camera Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HDMI and Composite/Component BNC Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>Supports up to Full HD 1080p60 Signals</li>\r\n	<li>800 x 480 Display Resolution</li>\r\n	<li>400cd/m&sup2; Brightness</li>\r\n	<li>600:1 Contrast Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>F-970 &amp; LP-E6 Battery Plates Included</li>\r\n	<li>AC Adapter Included</li>\r\n	<li>Built-In 1W Speaker &amp; Headphone Output</li>\r\n	<li>4 Assignable Function Buttons</li>\r\n	<li>Shoe Mount and Sunshade Included</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Lilliput 569/O is a compact 5&quot; on-camera monitor</strong>&nbsp;for setting up and monitoring your shots on a larger display. The 569/O offers HDMI input/output, Composite BNC input/output, and Component BNC input connections, providing for compatibility with different camera types. This monitor features an 800 x 480 display resolution and supports input resolutions up to Full HD 1080p60 via HDMI input.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This handy companion comes with several accessories that will allow for a comprehensive experience from the start. You get two different interchangeable battery plates, a robust sunshade, shoe mount adapter, HDMI cable, and AC power adapter for continuous in-studio power.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The 569/O has four assignable function buttons on the front, as well as input selection buttons that will let you switch between inputs if you have more than one connected. There&#39;s also a built-in speaker and headphone output on the front for monitoring audio while you shoot.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Key Features</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Supports up to Full HD 1080p60 resolution signals via HDMI input</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI input and output</li>\r\n	<li>Composite BNC input and output</li>\r\n	<li>Component on three BNCs</li>\r\n	<li>Audio input on BNC</li>\r\n	<li>1W speaker</li>\r\n	<li>Headphone output</li>\r\n	<li>800 x 480 display resolution</li>\r\n	<li>600:1 contrast ratio</li>\r\n	<li>400cd/m&sup2; brightness</li>\r\n	<li>F-970 and LP-E6 battery plates and AC power adapter included</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Buttons and Functions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>F1-F4 assignable buttons</li>\r\n	<li>Composite, Component, HDMI, and Power switchable buttons</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast</li>\r\n	<li>Saturation</li>\r\n	<li>Sharpness</li>\r\n	<li>Tint</li>\r\n	<li>Volume</li>\r\n	<li>Color mode</li>\r\n	<li>Camera</li>\r\n	<li>Mark</li>\r\n	<li>Underscan</li>\r\n	<li>Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>Blue Mode</li>\r\n	<li>Reset</li>\r\n	<li>Language</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCD Size 5&quot; (12.7 cm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Display Resolution 800 x 480</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inputs 1 x HDMI&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x Composite on BNC&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x Component on 3 BNC (YPbPr)&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x Audio on BNC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI Format Support 1080p/1080i/720p at 60/59.94/50 fps&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>480i at 60/59.94 fps&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>576i at 50 fps</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Active Area 4.25 x 2.55&quot; (108 x 64.8 mm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dot Pitch 0.135 x 0.135 mm</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aspect Ratio 16:9</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brightness 400 cd/m&sup2;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrast Ratio 600:1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Backlight LED</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Surface Treatment Antiglare, Hard-Coating (3H)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Response Time Typical: Tr: 2 ms, Tf: 6 ms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maximum: Tr: 4 ms, Tf: 12 ms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>View Angle 75/75&deg; (Left/Right) and 60/70&deg; (Up/Down)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outputs 1 x HDMI&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x Composite on BNC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power 6 to 24 VDC, DC power connector</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power Consumption &le;6 W</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SD 480i (60/59.94 Hz), 576i (50 Hz)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Speaker Built-in, 1 W</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Menu Language English/Chinese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Storage Temperature -22 to 158&deg;F (-30 to 70&deg;C)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operation Temperature -4 to 140&deg;F (-20 to +60&deg;C)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operating Humidity 0-90% RH</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dimensions 5.94 x 4.56 x 1.55&quot; (151 &times; 116 &times; 39.5 mm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>5.94 x 4.56 x 3.61&quot; (151 &times; 116 &times; 91.8 mm) with sunshade</p>\r\n', '1612201654235fda3bbfe728f.jpg', 8500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:54:23', 0, '2020-12-16 16:54:23'),
(149, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 569O/P นิ้ว Camera-Top Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ &nbsp;Lilliput 569O/P 5&quot; Camera-Top Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Lilliput 569O/P 5&quot; Camera-Top Monitor is a 16:9 LED</strong>&nbsp;field monitor with HDMI in &amp; out, component video, and sun hood. It comes with peaking and focus assist tools and is optimized for DSLR cameras. With 400 nits brightness, the monitor offers visibility even in challenging lighting conditions. The built-in 1W speaker outputs clear audio. This field monitor also provides advanced camera auxiliary functions such as peaking, false color, histogram, and exposure. It is great at displaying accurate images and makes photo &amp; recording even easier with its functionality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>5&quot; Monitor with Wide Screen Aspect Ratio</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The high resolution 5&quot; LCD displays pin-sharp images on a compact and lightweight monitor. It is ideal for customers looking for an external monitor that won&#39;t weigh them down.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Optimized for DSLR Cameras</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is the perfect external field monitor. Providing more screen real estate than the built-in LCD on most DSLRs and featuring some of the highest specifications found on a Lilliput monitor, this 5&quot; monitor is quickly becoming many DSLR users best friend.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Better Advanced Functions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Providing advanced camera auxiliary functions such as peaking, false color, histogram, and exposure are major concerns with DSLR users. This field monitor is great at displaying accurate images and makes photo &amp; recording even easier with its functionality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDMI Video Output</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This field monitor includes an HDMI-output feature which allows customers to duplicate the video content onto a second monitor without the need for an HDMI splitter. The second monitor can be any size and picture quality will not be affected.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>800 x 480 High Resolution</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Squeezing 384,000 pixels onto a 5&quot; LCD panel creates a pin-sharp picture. When your full 1080i/p content is scaled onto this monitor, the image quality is stunning and you can pick out every detail even on this compact monitor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>600:1 High Contrast Ratio</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With enhanced color representation and improved LED backlight technology, DSLR users can rejoice that what they see on the monitor is what they get in post-production.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Enhanced Brightness with Great Outdoor Performance</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Featuring a 400 cd/㎡ backlight, this field monitor produces a vivid and crystal clear picture. Your video content won&#39;t look washed out when this field monitor is used under sun light thanks to a boosted brightness LCD. The inclusive sun hood also provides even better outdoors performance.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Wide Viewing Angles</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>With a 150&deg; wide viewing angle, you can get the same vivid picture from wherever you are standing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Battery plates included</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>It includes two battery plates compatible with F970, LP-E6, DU21, and QM91D batteries.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>HDMI, Component, and Composite through BNC Connectors</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>No matter which camera or AV equipment you use with this field monitor, there is a video input to suit all applications. Most DSLR cameras ship with an HDMI output, but larger production cameras output HD component and regular composite through BNC connectors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>LCD Size 5.0&quot; (12.7 cm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Display Resolution 800 x 480 (Support up to 1920 &times; 1080)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Active Area H x V: 4.25 x 2.55&quot; (108.0 x 64.8 mm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dot Pitch H x V: 0.135 x 0.135 mm</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aspect Ratio 16:9</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brightness 400 cd/m&sup2;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrast Ratio 600:1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Light Source LED</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Surface Treatment Antiglare, Hard-Coating (3H)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Response Time Typical: Tr: 2 ms, Tf: 6 ms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maximum: Tr: 4 ms, Tf: 12 ms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>View Angle 75/75&deg; (Left/Right) and 60/70&deg; (Up/Down)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Interface Video input, video out, audio input, YPbPr, HDMI input, HDMI output, DC power</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Input Connector 1 x HDMI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x YPbPr</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x Video</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x DC power</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x Audio</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Output Connector 1 x HDMI 1 x Video</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Audio 1 x Built-in speaker</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x HDMI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power 6 to 24 VDC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power Consumption &le;6 W</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Control Basic: Video, YPbPr, power, and HDMI buttons; F1-F4 User-definable buttons; BRI/M/SEL and VOL/ADJ knobs&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Advanced: Brightness, contrast, saturation, sharpness, tint, volume, color mode, camera, mark, underscan, ratio, blue mode, reset, language</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Speaker Built-in 1 W</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Menu Language English / Chinese</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Storage Temperature -22 to 158&deg;F (-30 to 70&deg;C)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operation Temperature -4 to 140&deg;F (-20 to 60&deg;C)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At High Temperature: Ta= 60&deg;C</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operating Humidity 0 to 90% RH</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At High Humidity: 90% RH, 240 hours</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dimensions Without Sun Shade: 5.9 x 4.6 x 2&quot; (15.1 x 11.6 x 4 cm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Sun Shade: 5.9 x 4.5 x 3.6&quot; (15.1 x 11.6 x 9.2 cm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Weight Without Cover: 11.1 oz (316.0 g)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With Cover: 13.6 oz (386.0 g)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n', '1612201654525fda3bdcc3c99.jpg', 8500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:54:52', 0, '2020-12-16 16:54:52'),
(150, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput Q7 Full HD Monitor with SDI HDMI Cross Conversion (7นิ้ว)', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Lilliput Q7 Full HD Monitor with SDI &amp; HDMI Cross Conversion (7&quot;)</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Q7 Full HD Monitor with SDI &amp; HDMI</strong>&nbsp;Cross Conversion from Lilliput features a 7&quot; LCD panel with 1920 x 1200 resolution, 1000:1 contrast ratio, and 500 cd/m&sup2; brightness. It has an aspect ratio of 16:10 and 170&deg;/170&deg; wide viewing angles.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This field monitor comes integrated with advanced functions such as column YRGB (peak), timecode, waveform, vectorscope, and audio level meter. It also offers additional functions that can assist you in accurately monitoring while shooting video and playing back footage. These functions include pixel zoom, peaking, false color, histogram, exposure, check field, color bar, image flip, and pix-to-pix.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The high-quality HDMI and 3G-SDI</strong>&nbsp;inputs ensure that the precise color can be conveniently controlled under multiple displays. It comes with SDI and HDMI cross conversion that allows signal transmission from SDI input to HDMI out, and from HDMI input to SDI out. The monitor features a 0.9&quot; slim metal housing that protects it from vibration, drops, and adverse weather conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Full HD 1920 x 1200 resolution</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 500 cd/m&sup2;</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast ratio 1000:1</li>\r\n	<li>Waveform PIP mode</li>\r\n	<li>Column (YRGB peak), time code</li>\r\n	<li>Integrated recording information display</li>\r\n	<li>SDI and HDMI cross conversion</li>\r\n	<li>Slim metal housing 0.9&quot; (22 mm)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Display Screen 7&quot; (17.8 cm)</li>\r\n	<li>Display Resolution 1920 x 1200 (Dot)</li>\r\n	<li>Active Area (WxH) 151.2 x 94.5 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Dot Pitch W x H: 26.25 x 78.75 &micro;m</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:10</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast Ratio 500:1</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 500 cd/m&sup2;</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle 170&deg; / 170&deg; (H/V)</li>\r\n	<li>Light Source Single LED (side-light type)</li>\r\n	<li>Surface Treatment Hard coat on the polarizer (ATW)</li>\r\n	<li>Response Time Typical:</li>\r\n	<li>16 ms (Fall time)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Maximum:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>27 ms (Rise time)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>35 ms (Fall time)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Input 1 x 3G-SDI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x HDMI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Output 1 x 3G-SDI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x HDMI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Audio 1 x Speaker</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x 3.5 mm Mini jack</p>\r\n\r\n<p>SDI Formats Supported SMPTE-125M:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>480i (59.94)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SMPTE-274M:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1080i (60 / 59.94 / 50)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1080p (30 / 29.97 / 25 / 24 / 24sF / 23.98 / 23.98 sF)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SMPTE-292M:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1080p (30 / 29.97 / 25 / 24 / 24sF / 23.98 / 23.98 sF)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SMPTE-296M:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>720p (60 / 59.94 / 50 / 30 / 29 / 25 / 24 / 23.98)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SMPTE-372M:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>720p (60 / 59.94 / 50)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1080i (29.97 / 25 / 24 / 23.98)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1080p (60 / 59.94 / 50 / 30 / 29.97 / 25 / 24 / 23.98)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SMPTE-425M-AB:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1080p (60 / 59.94 / 50)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Level A &amp; Level B 720p (60 / 59.94 / 50 / 30 / 29.97 / 25 / 24 / 23.98)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Level B 2 x 1080i (60 / 59.94 / 50)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ITU-R BT.656:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>576i (50)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI Format Support 1080p, 1080i, 720p, 576p, 576i, 480p, 486i</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Current 1 A</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Input Voltage 7 to 24 VDC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power Consumption &le;13 W</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Storage Temperature -22 to 158&deg;F (-30 to 70&deg;C)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operation Temperature -4 to 140&deg;F (-20 to 60&deg;C)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operation Time 240 h at 140&deg;F (60&deg;C) and 90% RH</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dimensions (L x W x D) 7.2 x 4.9 x 0.9&quot; (182 x 124 x 22 mm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Weight 14 oz (405 g)</p>\r\n', '1612201655135fda3bf1ea0f0.jpg', 19500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:55:13', 0, '2020-12-16 16:55:13');
