(151, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput A7 7 นิ้ว Full HD Camera-Top Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput A7 7&quot; Full HD Camera-Top Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lilliput A7</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Lilliput A7 is the highest definition HDMI Monitor&nbsp;</strong>in our vast range. With a native definition of 1920 x 1200px, it has more than enough pixel density to accommodate any HDMI input feed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The full metal outer body protects the unit against bumps and scrapes and both BSW threads and VESA 75 mounting allow both for mobile work and for studio installation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Advanced monitor functionality</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>As detailed at the top of this description page, the Q7 has a plenitude of advanced functions to assist with your shooting. Namely - Timecodes, Columnar YRGB, Pixel Zoom Function, Vector Scopes, Waveforms, Audio Level Meters, Peaking, False Colour, Histograms, Exposures, Check Fields, Color Bars, Pixel to Pixel, and Image flips. A host of functions for a multi faceted monitoring solution.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7&quot; SDI monitor with widescreen aspect ratio</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Lilliput Q7 features our first full HD native panel, clocking in at 1920 x 1200. Much improved over its predecessors, this high resolution will give you the clearest view of your images without the need for down sampling or interpolation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Metal outer frame for added durability</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Q7 has a lightweight metal housing - designed to take the roughest of knocks while at the same time being as light and portable. The unit weight in at 405g, with an overall thickness of 22mm - far thinner and lighter than many other comparable models. Invaluable for use in the field, or in a tough-and-tumble environment.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Battery plate system for compatible batteries with your DSLR setup</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>We supply the monitor with 2 battery plates as standard - these are compatible with the Canon LP-E6 and the Sony F-970. Also available are the Sony QM91D and the Panasonic DU21, and for an addition charge we can supply a V-Mount battery plate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Shoe mount Adaptor included</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are two options for mounting this monitor - the most common is the Shoe Mount adaptor which screws into a 1/4&quot; BSW threaded hole at the bottom of the monitor and then clips into the shoe mount on top of your camera. Alternatively, you can use the VESA 75 mounting hole set in the back to attach the monitor to a sturdier mount if needed</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Screen Size (diagonal)&nbsp;7&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio&nbsp;16:10</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution (Pixels)&nbsp;1920x1200 (324ppi) (native</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle (degrees)&nbsp;170&ordm; x, 170&ordm; y</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness (cd/m&sup2;)&nbsp;500</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast Ratio&nbsp;1000:1</li>\r\n	<li>LCD Backlight&nbsp;LED</li>\r\n	<li>Video Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI x1</li>\r\n	<li>Video Outputs</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI x1</li>\r\n	<li>Audio Outputs</li>\r\n	<li>Built in speaker, 3.5mm Headphone Jack</li>\r\n	<li>Input Power Source</li>\r\n	<li>DC 12V</li>\r\n	<li>Operating Temperature</li>\r\n	<li>-20&ordm;C to 60&ordm;C</li>\r\n	<li>Mount Type</li>\r\n	<li>&frac14; inch BSW thread, VESA 75</li>\r\n	<li>Please note: product specifications, features, images and related downloads are subject to change at Lilliput UK&#39;s discretion at any time without prior notification. Lilliput UK Ltd cannot be held liable for outdated product information. Should customers have any queries about listed product specifications, please call Lilliput UK Ltd on +44 0845 0068868.</li>\r\n	<li>Home Monitors HDMI Monitors A7</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201655385fda3c0a6488e.jpg', 8900, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:55:38', 0, '2020-12-16 16:55:38'),
(152, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput Mopro 7 นิ้ว X-Sports Camera Monitor for GoPro Hero 3+, 4 & DSLR (Black)', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput Mopro 7&quot; X-Sports Camera Monitor for GoPro</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>7&quot; 1280 x 800 Native HDMI Monitor</li>\r\n	<li>Supports Up to 1920 x 1080</li>\r\n	<li>400 Nit / 800:1 Contrast Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>178&deg; H /V Viewing Angles</li>\r\n	<li>Interchangeable Rear Cover System</li>\r\n	<li>Internal GoPro Connection</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI &amp; Composite Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>Built-In 2600mAh Battery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The black Lilliput Mopro 7&quot; X-Sports Camera Monitor for GoPro Hero 3+, 4 &amp; DSLR</strong>&nbsp;features an interchangeable rear cover system that allows you to mount an optional GoPro 3+ or 4 camera within the monitor, or use the monitor as an on-camera field monitor. The interchangeable rear covers are what sets this monitor apart from other on-camera field monitors. The GoPro-compatible back allows you to mount your GoPro Hero 3+ or 4 into the monitor, providing you a 7&quot; viewing screen with a fully functioning GoPro camera embedded in the monitor.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The monitor features a native resolution of 1280 x 800 supporting resolutions up to 1920 x 1080 via scaling. With a brightness of 400 cd/m2 and 800:1 contrast, the monitor provides a bright, sharp image with good contrast. You can view the monitor from off-angle and still see an image with good contrast and color reproduction owing to the IPS panel.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Rear Covers</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The monitor features two interchangeable rear covers. Using the first cover, the monitor is a normal on-camera monitor with an HDMI and composite input. However, replacing the rear cover with the GoPro compatible cover allows you to embed your GoPro camera rearward facing so that you can hold the monitor, watch the footage, and have the camera shoot in the direction you are facing. An internal connector plugs into your GoPro and allows the monitor to display the camera&#39;s footage the footage, and the cover holds your camera securely and maintains the camera&#39;s functionality.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Monitor</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>7&quot; IPS panel 178&deg; wide viewing angles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1280 x 800 resolution</p>\r\n\r\n<p>400cd/m2 brightness</p>\r\n\r\n<p>800:1 contrast ratio</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Internal Battery</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The built-in 2600 mAh battery can run the monitor for up to five hours under normal conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Display</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Type 7&quot; IPS LCD</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LED backlit</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Resolution Native: 1280 x 800</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supports: 1920x1080</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Aspect Ratio 16:10</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brightness 400 cd/m2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrast Ratio 800:1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Viewing Angle (H/V) 178&deg; / 178&deg;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inputs/Outputs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inputs Internal</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x HDMI type D for GoPro only)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>External</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x HDMI type C</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x AV Connector (composite)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Outputs 1 x Earphone</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1 x Speaker</p>\r\n\r\n<p>General</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mounting Thread 1/4&quot;-20</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Current 480 mA</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Input Voltage 7 to 24 VDC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Battery Built-in 2600 mAh</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power Consumption &le;5.8 W</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Connector 1 x mini-USB (for GoPro charging)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operating Temperature -4 to 140&deg;F / -20 to 60&deg;C</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Storage Temperature -22 to 158&deg;F / -30 to 70&deg;C</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dimensions (L x W x H) GoPro Cover: 7.0 x 4.8 x 1.6&quot; / 179.0 x 121.0 x 40.5 mm</p>\r\n\r\n<p>DSLR Cover: 7.0 x 4.8 x 0.8&quot; / 179.0 x 121.0 x 21.0 mm</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Weight Including Battery: 14.8 oz / 420.0 g</p>\r\n', '1612201656495fda3c51149e1.jpg', 8500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:56:49', 0, '2020-12-16 16:56:49'),
(153, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 662S นิ้ว 3G-SDIHDMI Field Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput 662/S 7&quot; 3G-SDI/HDMI Field Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The 662/S 7&quot; 3G-SDI/HDMI</strong>&nbsp;Field Monitor from Lilliput is a 7&quot; widescreen metal framed LCD camera monitor with 3G-SDI and HDMI input and output. It offers 1280 x 800 resolution with 400 cd/m&sup2; brightness, an 800:1 contrast ratio, and features advanced functionality such as peaking, focus assist, waveform tools, and false color filters. The 662/S supports cross conversion between HDMI and SDI. You can input an SDI signal and receive HDMI output, and vice versa.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7&quot; IPS panel with 1280 x 800 resolution</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI output connector can actively transmit an HDMI input signal, or output an HDMI signal that has been converted from SDI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Features 3G-SDI, HDMI, and component and composite through BNC&nbsp;<strong>connectors</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Foldable sun hood becomes a screen protector</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI output feature allows customers to duplicate the video content onto a second monitor</p>\r\n\r\n<p>You can customize four programmable function buttons for shortcut operations according to different needs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monitor Type Widescreen</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Screen Size 7&quot; (18 cm)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Resolution Native: 1280 x 800</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Maximum: 1920 x 1080</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Display Scan Frequency 60 to 72 Hz</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Display Colors Not specified by manufacturer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Viewing Angle 178 x 178&deg;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brightness 400 cd/m2</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrast Ratio 800:1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Response Time 6 ms</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Inputs/Outputs Video In</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3G-SDI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>BNC component/composite</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Video Out</p>\r\n\r\n<p>3G-SDI</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI (HDMI-SDI cross conversion possible)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Audio Out</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Operating Temperature Not specified by manufacturer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power Requirements 12 VDC</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Power Consumption Not specified by manufacturer</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mount Type 1/4&quot;-20 threads, shoe mount</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dimensions (WxHxD) 7.6 x 5.9 x 5.5&quot; (19.2 x 15.2 x 14.1 cm) with cover</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7.6 x 5.9 x 1.2&quot; (19.2 x 15.2 x 3.1 cm) without cover</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Weight 14 oz (400 g)</p>\r\n', '1612201657145fda3c6a3a84e.jpg', 19500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:57:14', 0, '2020-12-16 16:57:14'),
(154, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 663/O/P2 7 นิ้ว LCD On-Camera HDMI Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput 663/O/P2 7&quot; LCD On-Camera HDMI Monitor&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>7&quot; 1280 x 800 IPS LCD Display</li>\r\n	<li>800:1 Contrast Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI, Component, Composite Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI Loop Output</li>\r\n	<li>Peaking, False Color, Histogram</li>\r\n	<li>Customizable Front Panel Buttons</li>\r\n	<li>Metal Chassis Sun Hood &amp; Tally Light</li>\r\n	<li>3 x 1/4&quot;-20 Threaded Mounting Holes</li>\r\n	<li>Sony L &amp; Canon LP-E6 Battery Plates</li>\r\n	<li>V-Mount &amp; Gold Mount Plate Adapter</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lilliput&#39;s 663/O/P2 7&quot; LCD On-Camera HDMI Monitor</strong>&nbsp;is an on-camera monitor offering 1280 x 800 resolution with 400 nit brightness and an 800:1 contrast ratio. The monitor allows you to analyze focus, exposure, and other characteristics with False Color, Pixel-to-Pixel, and Histogram. It supports both NTSC and PAL compatible signals with HDMI, Component, and Composite inputs. This monitor also features an HDMI output, allowing you to feed the monitor and send the video signal along an HDMI infrastructure. It also features both a built-in speaker and headphone jack.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The four front panel buttons and four rotating knobs can be assigned to specific functions that allow you to call up often-used menu functions. You can power the monitor by using the included battery plates or the 4-pin XLR connector. The included 4-pin XLR power cable features a barrel connector and three pigtail cables for connecting to a tally system. The monitor features a tally indicator on the front of the monitor. An assortment of supplied accessories includes a Sony L-type and Canon LP-E6-type battery plates. The monitor incorporates a 1/4&quot;-20 threaded mounting hole on the bottom and on each side, and the included sun hood attaches via hook and loop fastener to a removable sun hood attachment frame. A V-mount and Gold mount plate adapter allows you to mount optional V-mount or Gold mount battery plates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Assignable Function Buttons &amp; Knobs</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The front panel buttons and knobs can be customized to call up often-used menu functions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>F1 to F4 Buttons:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Center Marker</li>\r\n	<li>Check Field</li>\r\n	<li>Color Bar</li>\r\n	<li>Camera (format selection)</li>\r\n	<li>PIP</li>\r\n	<li>Flip</li>\r\n	<li>Zoom</li>\r\n	<li>Pixel-to-Pixel</li>\r\n	<li>Freeze</li>\r\n	<li>Input</li>\r\n	<li>Underscan</li>\r\n	<li>H/V Delay</li>\r\n	<li>Peaking</li>\r\n	<li>False Color</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure</li>\r\n	<li>Histogram</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>R1 to R4 Knobs</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Contrast</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness</li>\r\n	<li>Saturation</li>\r\n	<li>Tint</li>\r\n	<li>Volume</li>\r\n	<li>Sharpness</li>\r\n	<li>Back Light</li>\r\n	<li>Monitoring Features</li>\r\n	<li>Histogram</li>\r\n	<li>1:1 Pixel-to-Pixel</li>\r\n	<li>Picture-in-Picture (for when the HDMI and Composite inputs are used simultaneously)</li>\r\n	<li>H/V Delay</li>\r\n	<li>Underscan</li>\r\n	<li>Center Marker</li>\r\n	<li>Zoom (up to 8x)</li>\r\n	<li>False Color</li>\r\n	<li>Peaking</li>\r\n	<li>Color Bar</li>\r\n	<li>Image Flip</li>\r\n	<li>Freeze Input</li>\r\n	<li>Adjustable color temperature</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Peaking</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peaking highlights the sharpest (most in focus) areas of the image with a color outline. The monitor features two modes, monochrome, and color. The monochrome mode shows the image in black and white with the red peaking outline, and the color peaking mode shows the image in color with a red peaking outline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>False Color</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The False Color feature provides under/over luminance warning by presenting the image as a series of color values representing exposure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Waveform</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The waveform provides an objective evaluation of your video signal. It displays the brightness of your image on an IRE scale, allowing you to see if your image will clip, and where your black levels are.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Histogram</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Histogram provides a graphic depiction of how many pixels in your image are at each level between black and white. This provides you exposure information so you can objectively judge how much of your image is clipping, falling into the shadows, or being captured faithfully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Vectorscope</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The vectorscope displays the signal on a graph so you can check the phase of your colors. The vectorscope function also verifies and checks the overall tint and hue of an image.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1:1 Pixel Mode</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1:1 pixel-to-pixel mapping allows you to look at parts of your image without any scaling, so you can see the actual detail and not be fooled by scaling artifacts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>H/V Delay</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This mode allows you to see the video signal outside the active picture area. Settings include Off, H/V Delay, H Delay, and V Delay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Underscan/Overscan</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allows you to display an image with lower resolution than the screen with either a black border around the image or fill the screen entirely.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>LCD Display</li>\r\n	<li>LCD Size 7.0&quot; (17.8 cm) (IPS)</li>\r\n	<li>Display Resolution 1280 x R.G.B. x 800 (Dot)</li>\r\n	<li>Active Area 149.76 (H) x 93.6 (V) mm</li>\r\n	<li>Dot Pitch 0.117 (H) x 0.117 (V) mm</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:10</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 400 cd/m2</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast Ratio 800:1</li>\r\n	<li>Light Source LED</li>\r\n	<li>Surface Treatment Hard coating</li>\r\n	<li>Response Time TR: 15 ms (typical), 20 ms (maximum)</li>\r\n	<li>TF: 20 ms (typical), 30 ms (maximum)</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle Left/Right/Up/Down: 89&deg;</li>\r\n	<li>178&deg; wide viewing angle</li>\r\n	<li>Video</li>\r\n	<li>Input Signal Analog RGB</li>\r\n	<li>Interface HDMI, YPbPr, Video, Audio, XLR, DC Power, Earphone</li>\r\n	<li>Input / Output Connectors HDMI, YPbPr, Composite, Audio L&amp;R, TALLY</li>\r\n	<li>Output: HDMI</li>\r\n	<li>Format Support HDMI</li>\r\n	<li>Full HD: 1080p (60/59.94/50/30/29.97/25/24/23.98/23.976/24SF)</li>\r\n	<li>HD: 1018i (60/59.95/50), 1035i (60/59.94), 720p (60/59.94/50/30/29.97/25)</li>\r\n	<li>SD: 576p (50), 576i (50), 480p (60/59.94), 486i (60/59.94)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Control Basic: Video, YPbPr, HDMI&amp; SDI (no use). F1-F4 User-definable buttons, BRI/MENU knob, SAT knob, TINT knob, CONT knob</li>\r\n	<li>Advance: Brightness, Contrast, Saturation, Tint, Sharpness, Volume, Center Marker, Aspect Marker, Screen Marker, Marker Color, Marker Mat, Thickness, Check Field, Color Bar, Camera, PIP, Image Flip, Zoom, Pixel-to-Pixel, Freeze Input, Underscan, H/V delay, Peaking, False Color, Exposure, Histogram, Level Meter and Wave/Vector, Waveform Trans, Waveform Size, Language, SDI, Input Format OSD, LOGO, Manufacturer Default, Back Light, IPS</li>\r\n	<li>Speaker Built in, 1 W</li>\r\n	<li>Language English/Chinese</li>\r\n	<li>Power Requirements 7 to 24 VDC (XLR Connector)</li>\r\n	<li>Power Consumption &le;11 W</li>\r\n	<li>Temperature Operating: -4 to 140&deg;F (-20 to 60&deg;C)</li>\r\n	<li>Storage: -22 to 158&deg;F (-30 to 70&deg;C)</li>\r\n	<li>Operating Humidity 80% RH maximum</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions (WxHxD) Monitor Without Sun Hood: 7.5 x 6 x 1.2&quot; (191.5 x 152 x 31.0 mm)</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor With Sun Hood: 7.5 x 6 x 5.5&quot; (191.5 x 152 x 141.0 mm)</li>\r\n	<li>Case: 12.2 x 9.7 x 3.8&quot; (309.0 x 247.0 x 97.5 mm)</li>\r\n	<li>Weight Monitor Without Sun Hood: 1.7 lb (0.8 kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor With Sun Hood: 2.1 lb (0.9 kg)</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor with Suitcase: 4.8 lb (2.2 kg)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201657405fda3c841cdf9.jpg', 13500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:57:40', 0, '2020-12-16 16:57:40'),
