(157, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 664/W 7 นิ้ว FPV Monitor with 5.8 GHz Wireless Receiver', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput 664/W 7&quot; FPV Monitor with 5.8 GHz Wireless Receiver</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The 664/W 7&quot; FPV Monitor 5.8 GHz Wireless</strong>&nbsp;Receiver from Lilliput is built for first-person viewing (FPV) of the wireless AV feed. The monitor supports both NTSC and PAL signals and provides a composite AV input and wireless connectivity. The 7&quot; IPS display has a resolution of 1280 x 800 and a high 400 cdm2 brightness for use in sunny conditions. The 5.8 GHz wireless receiver has a range of up to 6561.7&#39;.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>7&quot; FPV monitor supports resolutions up to 1280 x 800</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Features a built-in 5.8 GHz wireless receiver with a range of up to 6561.7&#39;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Offers screen brightness of 400 cd/m2 and a contrast ration of 800:1</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Supports PAL / NTSC signals with automatic switching, anti-black, anti-blue, and anti-flash</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Features composite video AV inputs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Can be used with Li-ion batteries (not included)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Suitable for use in outdoor photography applications</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LCD Display</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>LCD Size 7.0&quot; (17.8 cm) IPS</li>\r\n	<li>Display Resolution 1280 x 800</li>\r\n	<li>Active Area 149.76 (H) x 93.6 (V) mm</li>\r\n	<li>Dot Pitch 0.117 (H) x 0.117 (V) mm</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:10</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 400 cd/m2</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast Ratio 800:1</li>\r\n	<li>Surface Treatment 3H</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle 178&deg;/178&deg;</li>\r\n	<li>Video</li>\r\n	<li>Input Signal Analog RGB</li>\r\n	<li>Inputs 1 x HDMI, 1 x Composite, 5.8 GHz Wireless AV, 1 x Shutter Port</li>\r\n	<li>Input Connectors HDMI, AV</li>\r\n	<li>Wireless Channels CH1: 5705 MHz, CH2: 5685 MHz, CH3: 5665 MHz, CH4: 5645 MHz, CH5: 5885 MHz, CH6: 5905 MHz, CH7: 5925 MHz, CH8: 5945 MHz</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>General</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Control Basic: Power, Shutter shortcut button, F1-F3 User-definable buttons, Enter button, Left/right selection key, Menu, circularly switch</li>\r\n	<li>Speaker Built in, 1 W</li>\r\n	<li>Language English/Chinese</li>\r\n	<li>Power Requirements 12 VDC, 1500 mA</li>\r\n	<li>Power Consumption &le; 12 W</li>\r\n	<li>Temperature Operating: -4 to 140&deg;F (-20 to 60&deg;C)</li>\r\n	<li>Storage: -22 to 158&deg;F (-30 to 70&deg;C)</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions (L x W x D) 7.2 x 5.1 x 0.9&quot; (18.5 x 13.1 x 2.3 cm)</li>\r\n	<li>Weight 0.9 lb (0.4 kg)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201659205fda3ce80ca33.jpg', 14500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:59:20', 0, '2020-12-16 16:59:20'),
(158, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 665/O/P Peaking Focus Video Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>Lilliput 665/O/P Peaking Focus Video Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>7&quot; 1024 x 600 TFT LED Backlit Display</li>\r\n	<li>800:1 Contrast Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI, Component, Composite Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI &amp; Composite Output</li>\r\n	<li>Peaking, False Color, Histogram</li>\r\n	<li>Customizable Front Panel Buttons</li>\r\n	<li>Metal Chassis &amp; Sun Hood</li>\r\n	<li>3 x 1/4&quot;-20 Threaded Mounting Holes</li>\r\n	<li>Sony L &amp; Canon LP-E6 Battery Plates</li>\r\n	<li>V-Mount &amp; Gold-Mount Plate Bracket</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lilliput&#39;s 665/O/P Peaking Focus Video Monitor</strong>&nbsp;is an on-camera monitor offering 1024 x 600 resolution with 250 nit brightness and an 800:1 contrast ratio. The monitor allows you to analyze focus, exposure, and other characteristics with False Color, Pixel-to-Pixel, and Histogram. It supports both NTSC and PAL compatible signals with HDMI, Component, and Composite inputs. This monitor also features an HDMI output, allowing you to feed the monitor and send the video signal along an HDMI infrastructure. It also features both a built-in speaker and headphone jack.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the face of the monitor are a power button, four input select buttons, four front panel buttons, and four rotating knobs. The four input select buttons are from left to right Composite, Component, HDMI, and SDI; however, the SDI button is not active as the monitor does not feature an SDI input. The four front panel buttons and four rotating knobs can be assigned to specific functions that allow you to call up often-used menu functions. You can power the monitor by using the included battery plates or an optional 4-pin XLR connector. An assortment of supplied accessories includes a Sony L-Series type and a Canon LP-E6 type battery plate, a removable sun hood, a V-mount and Gold-mount plate bracket that allows you to mount optional V-mount or Gold-mount battery plates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Assignable Function Buttons &amp; Knobs</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The front panel buttons and knobs can be customized to call up often-used menu functions.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>F1 to F4 Buttons:</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Center Marker</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Check Field</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Color Bar</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Camera (format selection)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>PIP</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Flip</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zoom</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pixel-to-Pixel</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Freeze</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Input</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Underscan</p>\r\n\r\n<p>H/V Delay</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peaking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>False Color</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Exposure</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Histogram</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>R1 to R4 Knobs</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Contrast</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Brightness</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Saturation</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Tint</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Volume</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sharpness</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Back Light</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Monitoring Features</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Histogram</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1:1 Pixel-to-Pixel</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Picture-in-Picture (for when the HDMI and Composite inputs are used simultaneously)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>H/V Delay</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Underscan</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Center Marker</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Zoom (up to 8x)</p>\r\n\r\n<p>False Color</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peaking</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Color Bar</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Image Flip</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Freeze Input</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Adjustable color temperature</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Peaking</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Peaking highlights the sharpest (most in focus) areas of the image with a color outline. The monitor features two modes, monochrome, and color. The monochrome mode shows the image in black and white with the red peaking outline and the color peaking mode shows the image in color with a red peaking outline.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>False Color</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The False Color feature provides under/over luminance warning by presenting the image as a series of color values representing exposure.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Histogram</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The Histogram provides a graphic depiction of how many pixels in your image are at each level between black and white. This provides you exposure information so you can objectively judge how much of your image is clipping, falling into the shadows, or being captured faithfully.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>1:1 Pixel Mode</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>1:1 pixel-to-pixel mapping allows you to look at parts of your image without any scaling, so you can see the actual detail and not be fooled by scaling artifacts.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>H/V Delay</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This mode allows you to see the video signal outside the active picture area. Settings include Off, H/V Delay, H Delay, and V Delay.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Underscan/Overscan</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Allows you to display an image with lower resolution than the screen with either a black border around the image or fill the screen entirely.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>LCD Size 7&quot;</li>\r\n	<li>Video System NTSC</li>\r\n	<li>PAL</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution 1024 x 600</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:9</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 250 nit</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast 800:1</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle 160&deg;/150&deg; (H/V)</li>\r\n	<li>Input and Output Connectors Input</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI: 1 x HDMI Type A</li>\r\n	<li>Component: 3 x BNC</li>\r\n	<li>Composite: 1 x BNC</li>\r\n	<li>Audio: 1 x BNC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Output</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>HDMI: 1 x HDMI Type A</li>\r\n	<li>Composite: 1 x BNC</li>\r\n	<li>Speaker: 1 x</li>\r\n	<li>Language English</li>\r\n	<li>Chinese</li>\r\n	<li>Power Connectors 1 x 4-pin XLR</li>\r\n	<li>1 x Battery plate slot</li>\r\n	<li>1 x Coax connector</li>\r\n	<li>Power Requirements 7 to 24 VDC</li>\r\n	<li>Current: 900 mA</li>\r\n	<li>Power Consumption &le;10 W</li>\r\n	<li>Temperature Operating: -4 to 140&deg;F / -20 to 60&deg;C</li>\r\n	<li>Storage: -22 to 158&deg;F / -30 to 70&deg;C</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions (WxHxD) Monitor Without Sun Hood: 7.7 x 5.9 x 1.5&quot; / 194.5 x 150 x 38.5 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor With Sun Hood: 7.7 x 5.9 x 6.2&quot; / 194.5 x 150 x 158.5 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Weight Monitor Without Sun Hood: 1.1 lb / 480 g</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor With Sun Hood: 1.4 lb / 640 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201659435fda3cffe7f76.jpg', 8900, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 16:59:43', 0, '2020-12-16 16:59:43'),
(159, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 667GL70NP/H/Y On-Camera Video Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput 667GL70NP/H/Y On-Camera Video Monitor&nbsp;</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>7&quot; 800 x 480 TFT LED Backlit Display</li>\r\n	<li>500:1 Contrast Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI, Component, Composite Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>Image Flip</li>\r\n	<li>Sun Hood &amp; IR remote Control</li>\r\n	<li>2 x Interchangeable Battery Plates</li>\r\n	<li>Battery Indicator Light, Power Selector</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Lilliput&#39;s 667GL70NP/H/Y On-Camera Video Monitor</strong>&nbsp;provides 800 x 480 resolution with 400 nit brightness and an 500:1 contrast ratio. It supports NTSC and PAL compatible signals and features HDMI, Component, and Composite inputs. It features a built-in speaker, a sun hood, and an IR remote control. On the face of the monitor are the IR receiver, a battery power indicator, volume up and down buttons, a menu button, left/right select buttons, input select and a power button.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The monitor provides you control over the display&#39;s brightness, contrast, saturation, tint, and color temperature. You can power the monitor by using the included battery plates, an optional 4-pin XLR connector, or the built-in coax connector. An assortment of supplied accessories includes a Sony QM91D type and a Panasonic DU21 type battery plate, and a removable sun hood. The included mounting bracket is designed to allow you to stand the monitor on a desk. For on-camera mounting, you will require an optional cold shoe adapter.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>LCD Size 7&quot;</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Video System NTSC</li>\r\n	<li>PAL</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution 800 x 480</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:9</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 450 nit</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast 500:1</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle 140&deg;/120&deg; (H/V)</li>\r\n	<li>Input and Output Connectors Input</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI: 1 x HDMI Type A</li>\r\n	<li>Component: 3 x BNC</li>\r\n	<li>Composite: 2 x BNC</li>\r\n	<li>Audio: 1 x BNC</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Output</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Speaker: 1 x W</li>\r\n	<li>Input Resistance 75 &Omega;</li>\r\n	<li>Mounting 3 x 1/4&quot;-20 threaded mounting holes</li>\r\n	<li>Language English</li>\r\n	<li>Chinese</li>\r\n	<li>Power Connectors 1 x 4-pin XLR</li>\r\n	<li>1 x Battery plate slot</li>\r\n	<li>1 x Coax connector</li>\r\n	<li>Power Requirements 7 to 24 VDC</li>\r\n	<li>Operating Current: 650 mA</li>\r\n	<li>Max Standby Current: 50 mA</li>\r\n	<li>Power Consumption Max: 8 W</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions (WxHxD) Monitor Without Sun Hood: 7.4 x 5.2 x 1.3&quot; / 188 x 131 x 33 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor With Sun Hood: 7.6 x 5.3 x 2.9&quot; / 194 x 134 x 73 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Weight Monitor Without Sun Hood: 1.1 lb / 510 g</li>\r\n	<li>Monitor With Sun Hood: 1.5 lb / 668 g</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201700095fda3d196058b.jpg', 8500, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 17:00:09', 0, '2020-12-16 17:00:09'),
(160, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 668 7 นิ้ว HDMI On-Camera Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput 668 7 นิ้ว &nbsp;HDMI On-Camera Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>7&quot; 800 x 480 Display</li>\r\n	<li>HDMI, YPbPr, Composite Inputs</li>\r\n	<li>Built-In Battery</li>\r\n	<li>140&deg; Horizontal Viewing Angle</li>\r\n	<li>Includes Ball Mount and Sun Hood</li>\r\n	<li>Includes HDMI Cable</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>With inputs supporting analog and digital sources, this 7&quot; HDMI On-Camera Monitor from Lilliput provides an 800x480 pixel display for checking your image&#39;s focus and exposure. The display&#39;s 16:9 aspect ratio fits most signals output from HD camcorders without letterboxing or pillarboxing the image, ensuring the full screen resolution is used.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>On the rear panel, the HDMI input supports DSLR cameras and newer camcorders with HDMI outputs, up to 1080p resolution. For legacy cameras and analog equipment, a component YPbPr as well as dual composite video BNC inputs are also available.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For wide viewing angles and accurate colors, this monitor features an IPS display with an anti-glare finish and a 500:1 contrast ratio for punchy images. A sun hood is included for preventing excess glare when outdoors.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For power, a built-in battery can provide up to 3 hours of use on a full charge. Alternatively a 6-20 VDC power source can be input via the barrel jack. A ball mount is also included for securing the monitor atop a camera using an available shoe-mount.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7&quot; camera-top monitor with 16:9 aspect ratio</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>500:1 contrast ratio produces vivid and rich colors</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Enhanced 450 cd/m2 backlight produces a crystal clear picture and shows colors vividly</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>IPS panel offers 130&deg; horizontal and 120&deg; vertical wide viewing angles</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Built-in 2,200mAh Li-ion battery</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Shoe mount adapter included</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>LCD Display</li>\r\n	<li>LCD Size 7&quot; (18 cm)</li>\r\n	<li>Display Resolution 800 x 480</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:9</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 450 cd/m2</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast Ratio 500:1</li>\r\n	<li>Backlight White LED</li>\r\n	<li>Surface Treatment Anti-glare</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle 70/70&deg; (left/right) and 50/70&deg; (up/down)</li>\r\n	<li>Video</li>\r\n	<li>Interface Video, AV1, AV2, YPbPr, HDMI, DC power</li>\r\n	<li>Input Connectors Composite (BNC), YPbPr (BNC), HDMI</li>\r\n	<li>Input Format Support HDMI Format Support:</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>FULL HD: 1080p (60/59.94/50)</li>\r\n	<li>HD: 1080i (60/59.95/50), 720p (60/59.94/50)</li>\r\n	<li>SD: 480i (60/59.94), 576i (50)</li>\r\n	<li>General</li>\r\n	<li>Control Basic: -Volume down,+ Volume up, menu, 2 x selection key, switch key, power</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Advance: Brightness, Contrast, Saturation, Tint, OSD H-Position, OSD V-Position, Reset, Color Temperature, Red, Green, Blue, Language, Miscellaneous, Exit, Image Flip, Aspect Ratio, Sharpness, OSD duration.</li>\r\n	<li>Speaker Built in, 1 W</li>\r\n	<li>Battery 7.4 VDC, 2200 mAh</li>\r\n	<li>Power Consumption Max: 8 W</li>\r\n	<li>Environmental Operating: -4 to 140&deg;F (-20 to 60&deg;C)</li>\r\n	<li>Storage: -22 to 158&deg;F (-30 to 70&deg;C)</li>\r\n	<li>&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Operating at High Temperature and High Humidity: 140&deg;F (60&deg;C) / 90% RH max, 240 hrs</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions (L x W x D) 7.1 x 5.1 x 1.2&quot; / 188 x 131 x 33 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Weight 2.8 lb / 1.3 kg</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201700295fda3d2d8e681.jpg', 0, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 17:00:29', 0, '2020-12-16 17:00:29'),
(161, '', 'จำหน่าย Lilliput 5D-ii/O/P 7 นิ้ว HDMI LCD Field Monitor', 6, 19, '', 'จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput', '', '<h2>รายละเอียดสินค้า</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>จอมอนิเตอร์ Lilliput 5D-ii/O/P 7&quot; HDMI LCD Field Monitor</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>PRODUCT HIGHLIGHTS</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>7&quot; 1024 x 600 HDMI Monitor</li>\r\n	<li>False Color / Zebra / Histogram</li>\r\n	<li>250 cd/m&sup2; / 800:1 Contrast Ratio</li>\r\n	<li>130&deg; L / R Viewing Angle</li>\r\n	<li>Peaking / 1:1 Pixel Mapping</li>\r\n	<li>Integrated Collapsble Sunhood</li>\r\n	<li>Cold Shoe Mount</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The 5D-ii/O/P 7&quot; HDMI LCD Field Monitor</strong>&nbsp;from Lilliput is suitable for use with DSLR cameras and can be easily stored in a camera bag. It supports video with resolution up to 1920 x 1080 and features a native resolution of 1024 x 600, scaling your input video to fit. The 800:1 contrast ratio and 250 cd/m&sup2; brightness provide a sharp, clear display.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The monitor is equipped with 1:1 pixel mapping, peaking, and a foldable sun-hood/screen protector. It features an HDMI output, allowing you to feed a second monitor without requiring a splitter, thus reducing the amount of cable clutter on your camera. Four assignable front panel buttons allow you to rapidly recall often used menu functions. The monitor comes with Canon LP-E6 and Sony F970 battery plates.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>7&quot; LCD monitor fit for DSLR use</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Easily stored in a camera bag</p>\r\n\r\n<p>1:1 pixel mapping allows you to maintain the original resolution of your camera&#39;s output and avoid any unexpected focus issues in post-production</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Focusing is easier with the peaking functionality</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Screen protector folds out to become a sun hood, providing protection for the LCD and eliminating the need to buy a separate sun hood</p>\r\n\r\n<p>HDMI output feature allows duplication of the video content onto a second monitor without the need of any HDMI splitters</p>\r\n\r\n<p>LED-backlit display panels deliver higher levels of detail and image accuracy</p>\r\n\r\n<p>800:1 contrast ratio produces colors that are vivid, rich, and accurate</p>\r\n\r\n<p>With 150&deg; viewing angle, you can get the same vivid picture from wherever you are standing</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>SPECIFICATIONS</strong></em></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Screen Size (Diagonal) 7&quot; (177.8 mm)</li>\r\n	<li>Aspect Ratio 16:9</li>\r\n	<li>Resolution 1024 &times; 600 (native), 1920 &times; 1080 (maximum)</li>\r\n	<li>Pixel Pitch 0.135 &times; 0.135 mm</li>\r\n	<li>Display Scan Frequency 60 to 72 Hz</li>\r\n	<li>Response Time 6 ms</li>\r\n	<li>Viewing Angle 150 x 130&deg;</li>\r\n	<li>Brightness 250 cd/m&sup2;</li>\r\n	<li>Contrast Ratio (Typical) 800:1</li>\r\n	<li>LCD Backlight LED</li>\r\n	<li>Video Inputs HDMI</li>\r\n	<li>Video Outputs HDMI</li>\r\n	<li>Audio Outputs &lt; 1 W</li>\r\n	<li>Input Power 12 VDC</li>\r\n	<li>Mount Type 1/4&quot; BSW thread, shoe mount</li>\r\n	<li>Battery Plate Canon LP-E6: EOS 5D Mark II, EOS 5D Mark III, EOS 7D, EOS 60D, EOS 6D</li>\r\n	<li>Sony F970: DCR-TRV series, DCR-TRV E series, VX2100E PD P series, GV-A700, GV-D800 FD/CCD-SC/TR3/FX1E/HVR-AIC, HDR-FX1000E, HVR-Z1C, HVR-V1C, FX7E F330</li>\r\n	<li>Dimensions (W x H x D) 7.7 x 5.7 x 1.2&quot; (196.5 x 145 x 31 mm)</li>\r\n	<li>Weight 14.1 oz (400 g)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n', '1612201700545fda3d4626a53.jpg', 10900, 0, 0, '2020-12-16 17:00:54', 0, '2020-12-16 17:00:54');
